The Armed Forces operating in Zamfara State says it has killed a notorious bandit’s leader, Hassan Dan tagwaye and his twin, Hussaini. A statement signed by the coordinator, Defence Media Operations, Maj. Gen. John Enenche, and made available to newsmen in Gusau, yesterday, revealed the bandit’s leader and his twin brother were killed in Domboru forest in Zurmi local government area of the state. Recall Hassan Dan tagwaye, in August, granted full interview to Punch Newspaper on August 17, 2019, where he confessed, they kill 50 people for every slain herdsman. The statement further added, “The air strikes which was executed on June 23 have also resulted in the neutralization of several bandits.” According to it, the air component dispatched an enhanced force package of fighter jets and helicopter gunships to attack the location where many bandits who assembled for a meeting in one of their huts were killed. “The attack aircraft engaged the target structures, scoring accurate hits and taking out the huts along with their occupants. The NAF jets also later recorded direct hits on the suspected bunker, from where some of the bandits were seen emerging, completely destroying it. “Human Intelligence reports later confirmed that Hassan Tagwaye, leader of the bandits and his twin brother Hussaini along with several other bandits were neutralized in the air strikes, while a few escaped with injuries,” it said. The statement called on the general public to continue assisting the military with credible information in its efforts to rid the state of banditry activities.  